description: Botnia Exploration Holding AB engages in the exploration of gold, and other precious and base metals. The company is headquartered in Nacka Strand, Stockholm and currently employs 1 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2009-12-14. The firm focuses primarily on gold, as well as explores other precious and base metals. Its project portfolio consists of approximately 30 exploration licenses, such as Forsheden nr 1, Granberget nr 1, Rortjarnen nr 1, Stenberget nr 3 and Svanaberget nr 1, among others, as well as one mining concession, Vargbacken K nr 1. The firm operates two wholly-owned subsidiaries: Botnia Exploration AB and Hans. A. Resources Sweden AB. The firm is responsible for the group management functions, while its operational activities are conducted by the subsidiaries. The firm's shareholders comprise Akilakonsulting AB, Need Invest AB and Ramab Iggesund AB, among others.
name: Botnia Exploration Holding AB (publ)
